@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@
+# Per-Request Rollout Seed
+
+By default, verl does not set `SamplingParams.seed` per prompt unless
+`full_determinism` injects its deterministic per-replica fallback seed. With
+`actor_rollout_ref.rollout.per_request_seed=true`, each rollout request receives
+a deterministic seed derived from the base rollout seed, prompt index,
+`rollout_n`, and global step.
+
+```bash
+python3 -m verl.trainer.main_ppo \
+  actor_rollout_ref.rollout.per_request_seed=true \
+  actor_rollout_ref.rollout.seed=42 \
+  ...
+```
+
+The request seed is applied only when `temperature > 0`. Greedy requests keep
+their existing behavior.
+
+`sample_index` may be an integer dataset index or an opaque string (e.g. UUID
+from TransferQueue); non-numeric strings are hashed to a stable 31-bit integer
+before entering the formula.
+
+The seed formula is:
+
+```text
+seed = (base_seed + sample_index * 1000003 + rollout_n * 1009 + global_step * 9176) & 0x7FFFFFFF
+```
+
+This setting is independent from `full_determinism`. When both are enabled,
+`per_request_seed` sets `SamplingParams.seed` before the request reaches vLLM,
+and the existing `full_determinism` fallback does not overwrite it.
